<title>INDIA: Indian gold, silver trade closed on holiday.</title>
<headline>Indian gold, silver trade closed on holiday.</headline>
<dateline>BOMBAY 1996-08-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>India's bullion markets were closed on Thursday for the Parsi New Year, dealers said.</p>
<p>Trading will resume on Friday.</p>
<p>On Wednesday, gold was up by 10 rupees per 10 grammes and silver gained by 45 rupees per kg.</p>
<p>Prices of a gold biscuit (116.50 grammes) were up by 100 rupees.</p>
<p>-- Bombay Commodities +91-22-265 9000</p>
</text>
